      "body": "Dear Jeffrey N Lee-Chan,

I hope you are doing well.

This reporting is *not a tax matter*, but a *licensing matter*. We are
sending you this email because the penalties for not filing this report
might be high and we are trying to help you avoid those penalties with
information on how to file the business license renewal. Please contact the
city of LA for more information through
http://finance.lacity.org/locationshours


*PLEASE NOTE: The information below is for the City of Los Angeles ONLY.
Please be aware that if you work in a different city, you MUST obtain a
business license with that city and renew it in accordance with their
guidelines.*

*You need to have a business license if your business is located **within
the City of Los Angeles* *OR if you provide services within the City of Los
Angeles. Ex: a contractor located in Long Beach who performs services in
Los Angeles city is REQUIRED to obtain a business license with both the
city of Long Beach and the city of LA.*

*Please check here for city of LA limits **at **the following link *
https://finance.lacity.org/business-location


If you have a Business License with the City of Los Angeles, you should
have received the 2026 business renewal form (or a yellow postcard), *you
should file it by Monday, 3/2/2026*, to avoid late filing penalties and
interest.



If you did not receive a yellow postcard or renewal form notifying you of
this, please call the City of Los Angeles Office of Finance at (844)
663-4411.



If you worked in the City of Los Angeles during 2025 and did not register
for a business license, you still have to follow the above instructions and
register with the City of Los Angeles, the best way to do so is by going to
one of the field offices http://finance.lacity.org/locationshours



You can file the renewal online at the following link
<https://latax.lacity.org/laweb/F-logon.jsp>
https://latax.lacity.org/laweb/F-logon.jsp



In order to renew your business license, youâ€™ll need the following:



Account number

Business Address

2025 Gross income amount

*2025 Gross income generated in the City of LA **



*The tax liability is calculated in accordance with your income generated
IN and OUT of the City of Los Angeles.



There is an exemption for businesses that generated less the $100,000 in
the City of Los Angeles.

If you had to reimburse a client for a return, the gross income should
reflect this.



 *If your Income inside the limits of the City of Los Angeles is less than
$100,000, youâ€™ll be exempt from tax, BUT you still have to file it by the
due date, or youâ€™ll be assessed with Penalties and Interest, and your
Exemption will expire*.



Sometimes, when the Worldwide income (in and outside of LA) is more than
$100,000, even if the LA income is less than the $100,000, the exemption
will not apply, and the tax will be calculated on the amount you entered as
your Los Angeles Income.



If you feel you need assistance, contact the City of Los Angeles at (844)
663-4411.



*Even if you owe no tax, you must submit a completed renewal electronically
or by mail no later than February 29, 2026. *



*If you need help filing the renewal, feel free to call us at **(323)
433-4363**, before February 7, 2026, our fees for filling are $275. We will
be unable to help you file this renewal in a timely manner after February
7, 2026.*



Best Regards,

Los Angeles, CA 90048
